exports[`Etc Clobber Error 1`] = `"<div style="width: 280px; height: 400px; position: relative;"><div class="absolute inset-0 z-10 flex items-center justify-center bg-background/95 backdrop-blur-sm"><div class="h-full w-full max-h-[600px] max-w-[800px] p-5"><div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-white/10 p-6" style="background: radial-gradient(at 50% 100%, rgba(30, 30, 30, 0.98) 0%, rgba(20, 20, 20, 0.95) 50%, rgba(15, 15, 15, 0.92) 100%);"><div class="min-h-0 flex-1"><div class="flex h-full flex-col items-center justify-center gap-5" style="opacity: MOTION;"><div class="flex h-14 w-14 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-rose-300/10"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-triangle-alert h-7 w-7 text-rose-300" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m21.73 18-8-14a2 2 0 0 0-3.48 0l-8 14A2 2 0 0 0 4 21h16a2 2 0 0 0 1.73-3"></path><path d="M12 9v4"></path><path d="M12 17h.01"></path></svg></div><h2 class="text-center font-semibold text-white text-lg">Existing /etc files would be overwritten</h2><div class="w-full max-w-xl"></div><p class="max-w-xl rounded-lg border border-teal-400/30 bg-teal-400/10 px-4 py-2 text-center font-medium text-sm text-teal-200">No changes were made to your system.</p><div class="space-y-3"><div class="w-full max-w-xl overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-amber-300/20 bg-amber-300/5 text-left"><div class="border-amber-300/15 border-b px-4 py-3"><p class="font-medium text-amber-100 text-sm">3 /etc files need your review</p><p class="mt-1 text-amber-100/70 text-xs">Checked 12 managed entries before activation.</p></div><ul class="max-h-44 divide-y divide-white/10 overflow-y-auto"><li class="space-y-2 px-4 py-3"><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2"><code class="min-w-0 flex-1 truncate rounded bg-black/30 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-amber-50 text-xs">/etc/nix/github-token.conf</code><span class="shrink-0 rounded-full border border-amber-300/25 bg-amber-300/10 px-2 py-0.5 font-medium text-[10px] text-amber-100 uppercase tracking-wide">Unrecognized content</span></div><p class="text-[11px] text-zinc-300">nix-darwin does not recognize this file as one it can safely adopt.</p></li><li class="space-y-2 px-4 py-3"><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2"><code class="min-w-0 flex-1 truncate rounded bg-black/30 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-amber-50 text-xs">/etc/synthetic.conf</code><span class="shrink-0 rounded-full border border-amber-300/25 bg-amber-300/10 px-2 py-0.5 font-medium text-[10px] text-amber-100 uppercase tracking-wide">Not a regular file</span></div><p class="text-[11px] text-zinc-300">nix-darwin only adopts regular files or the exact expected symlink.</p><p class="truncate text-[11px] text-zinc-500">Current link: <code>/private/etc/synthetic.conf</code></p></li><li class="space-y-2 px-4 py-3"><div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2"><code class="min-w-0 flex-1 truncate rounded bg-black/30 px-2 py-1 font-mono text-amber-50 text-xs">/etc/pam.d/sudo_local</code><span class="shrink-0 rounded-full border border-amber-300/25 bg-amber-300/10 px-2 py-0.5 font-medium text-[10px] text-amber-100 uppercase tracking-wide">Unreadable</span></div><p class="text-[11px] text-zinc-300">nixmac could not inspect this path, so it is treated as unsafe.</p></li></ul></div></div><p class="max-w-xl text-center text-sm text-zinc-300">nix-darwin found files in /etc it doesn't manage and won't overwrite. Back up anything important, then rename each listed file by adding .before-nix-darwin to the end and retry. No changes were made to your system.</p></div><div class="flex h-full w-full flex-col" style="display: none !important;"><div class="mb-4 flex items-center justify-end"><button class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center whitespace-nowrap font-medium outline-none transition-all focus-visible:b